   <text>
      <front>
         <div1 type="abstract" n="1">
            <head>
               <bibl>
                  <abbr>ALS</abbr>
                  <extent>4 pp.</extent>
                  <date value="1839-11-19">19 November 1839</date>
                  <idno rend="suppress">SPEC.MMS.138_2</idno>
                  <title>Letter from Sophia Hawthorne to Elizabeth Peabody</title>
               </bibl>
            </head>
            <p>Sophia describes events surrounding her brother George's last illness, including a visit from Rev. Edward Thomson Taylor.</p>
         </div1>
      </front>
      <body>
         <div1 type="letter" n="1">
            <head></head>

<!-- Page 1 -->
<pb mmid="/5/5e42ca89-802c-4893-97f6-10f789789b0c" n="1"/>

            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date value="1839-11-19">Tuesday 1/2 4. Nov<abbr expan="ember">ember</abbr> 19th
<handShift old="SPH" new="Unknown"/>1839</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My dear <name type="recipient">Lizzie,</name>
                  <seg>
                     <note target="n1">1</note>
                  </seg>
               </salute>
            </opener>

<p n="1" id="L002P001">
<lb id="L02L001" n="001"/>I suppose that <name type="person" reg="Edward Thomson Taylor (1793-1871)" key="ETT">Mr. Taylor</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n2">2</note>
               </seg> has
<lb id="L02L002" n="002"/>told you of <name type="person" reg="Peabody, George" key="GP">George</name>'s <seg>
                  <note target="n3">3</note>
               </seg> perfect frame
<lb id="L02L003" n="003"/>of mind &mdash; of his experience of
<lb id="L02L004" n="004"/>that divine glow which was so
<lb id="L02L005" n="005"/>unaccountable &mdash; but so sweet &amp;
<lb id="L02L006" n="006"/>refreshing to him &mdash; &amp; seemed so like
<lb id="L02L007" n="007"/>an intimation from GOD that
<lb id="L02L008" n="008"/>it was well with him &mdash;; but he
<lb id="L02L009" n="009"/>would not tell you how like
<lb id="L02L010" n="010"/>a tender &amp; strong angel he <add place="infralinear" hand="SPH"> &#94;</add>
               <add place="supralinear" hand="SPH"> himself </add> was
<lb id="L02L0011" n="011"/>to us all &mdash; what a wonderful
<lb id="L02L0012" n="012"/>prayer he offered &mdash; which seemed
<lb id="L02L0013" n="013"/>to bring the host of heaven
<lb id="L02L0014" n="014"/>down to watch &amp; duly ward -
<lb id="L02L0015" n="015"/>which brought heaven into
<lb id="L02L0016" n="016"/>
               <name type="person">George</name>'s chamber &amp; carried us
<lb id="L02L0017" n="017"/>all as on Dove's wings into
<lb id="L02L0018" n="018"/>the spiritual world.  It was the
<lb id="L02L0019" n="019"/>most fervid &mdash; the most affectionate,
<lb id="L02L020" n="020"/>tender &amp; divine uplifting of 
<lb id="L02L021" n="021"/>soul to the infinite father &mdash;
<lb id="L02L022" n="022"/>that I ever heard.  He prayed for 
<lb id="L02L023" n="023"/>each &mdash; for the <q>Mother, <seg>
                     <note target="n4">4</note>
                  </seg> the tender
<lb id="L02L024" n="024"/>Mother &mdash; who hung around her life</q>
<lb id="L02L025" n="025"/>for the Father's <seg>
                  <note target="n5">5</note>
               </seg> manly heart &mdash;
<lb id="L02L026" n="026"/>for the sister <seg>
                  <note target="n6">6</note>
               </seg> whose duty called
<lb id="L02L027" n="027"/>her away &mdash; <q> &amp; oh bless &mdash; <hi rend="underline">our dear <name type="person">Mary</name>
                     <seg>
                        <note target="n7">7</note>
                     </seg></hi>
<!-- Page 2 -->
<pb mmid="/0/022feeb4-0e17-4d03-a876-dd5a73b13a27" n="2"/>
                  
<lb id="L02L028" n="028"/>he said &mdash; let not that peaceful
<lb id="L02L029" n="029"/>stream be disturbed &mdash; </q> " he prayed
<lb id="L02L030" n="030"/>for the sister present<seg>
                  <note target="n8">8</note>
               </seg>  &mdash; 'she with
<lb id="L02L031" n="031"/>the delicate nerves &mdash;' For <name type="person">Aunt
<lb id="L02L032" n="032"/>Pickman</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n9">9</note>
               </seg> too he petitioned
<lb id="L02L033" n="033"/>heaven &mdash;     The tears were at
<lb id="L02L034" n="034"/>last loosened from my brain
<lb id="L02L035" n="035"/>which I had kept back so long
<lb id="L02L036" n="036"/>that I began to feel as if they
<lb id="L02L037" n="037"/>were accumulating there &mdash;
<lb id="L02L038" n="038"/>&amp; they flowed down my face
<lb id="L02L039" n="039"/>like a summer rain without
<lb id="L02L040" n="040"/>convulsion.  After he rose
<lb id="L02L041" n="041"/>from his knees, <name type="person">George</name> stretched 
<lb id="L02L042" n="042"/>out his arms &amp; Mr. Taylor
<lb id="L02L043" n="043"/>clasped him to his heart in
<lb id="L02L044" n="044"/>a long, long embrace &mdash; Every
<lb id="L02L045" n="045"/>moment ejaculating "The Lord
<lb id="L02L046" n="046"/>bless you!  Bless you!  Bless you!"
<lb id="L02L047" n="047"/>in such a thrilling tone that
<lb id="L02L048" n="048"/>it seemed as if blessings must
<lb id="L02L049" n="049"/>come in legions at the call &mdash;
<lb id="L02L050" n="050"/>
               <name type="person">George</name>'s thin white hands were

<!-- Page 3 -->
<pb mmid="/6/68d56136-930a-47b7-ba9f-e4b3602eb38c" n="3"/>

<lb id="L02L051" n="051"/>so firmly fastened round his neck
<lb id="L02L052" n="052"/>that I thought he would never
<lb id="L02L053" n="053"/>let the angel go &mdash; even after he
<lb id="L02L054" n="054"/>had blessed him &mdash; but at last
<lb id="L02L055" n="055"/>he relaxed his hold. Then <name type="person">
                  <sic corr="Mr.">Mr</sic>
<lb id="L02L056" n="056"/>Taylor</name> turned to me &amp; took both
<lb id="L02L057" n="057"/>hands. <q>Be strong</q> said he. <q>
                  <hi rend="underline">It is</hi>
<lb id="L02L058" n="058"/><hi rend="underline">very pleasant on the other side</hi>. Be
<lb id="L02L059" n="059"/>quiet <del hand="SPH" type="overwritten">a</del>like a May morning.</q>
               <lb id="L02L060" n="060"/>He came with me into my room.
<lb id="L02L061" n="061"/>
               <q>Oh <name type="person">George</name> is a perfect lamb! A
<lb id="L02L062" n="062"/>perfect lamb. He is moonlight &mdash;
<lb id="L02L063" n="063"/>so clear &mdash; mild &mdash; I would not but
<lb id="L02L064" n="064"/>have seen him for the world. It
<lb id="L02L065" n="065"/>was worth coming just to look at
<lb id="L02L066" n="066"/>him. He never looked so handsome
<lb id="L02L067" n="067"/>in his life. There is no distortion
<lb id="L02L068" n="068"/>there. All is right. All is right.</q>
<lb id="L02L069" n="069"/>I cannot tell you all he said now.
<lb id="L02L070" n="070"/>Oh he is the most helpful &mdash; the
<lb id="L02L071" n="071"/>divinest spirit &mdash; is he not?
<lb id="L02L072" n="072"/>
               <name type="person">George</name> said there could not be such
<lb id="L02L073" n="073"/>a prayer conceived of. <q>
                  <name type="person">Mr. Taylor</name>
 <lb id="L02L074" n="074"/>is no sham</q> &mdash; he said.
<lb id="L02L075" n="075"/>
               <name type="person">George</name> is very much revived this
<lb id="L02L076" n="076"/>afternoon. He had not a bad
<lb id="L02L077" n="077"/>chill this morning &mdash; hardly any &mdash; &amp;
<lb id="L02L078" n="078"/>yesterday it was
<lb id="L02L079" n="079"/>two hours long 

<!--Page 4 -->
<pb mmid="/8/8f5d4ec8-e235-477b-a9f4-5f7b29094cf1" n="4"/>

<lb id="L02L080" n="080"/>
               <name>Mary</name> came today &amp; staid two hours
<lb id="L02L081" n="081"/>I carried her your letter this afternoon
<lb id="L02L082" n="082"/>&amp; she had <sic corr="received">recieved</sic> no harm.
<lb id="L02L083" n="083"/>
               <name type="person">George</name> thinks it would not be
<lb id="L02L084" n="084"/>right for you to come on
<lb id="L02L085" n="085"/>Wednesday. He thinks of
<lb id="L02L086" n="086"/>every thing in all relations
<lb id="L02L087" n="087"/>with exactest precision.
<lb id="L02L088" n="088"/>Yesterday he wandered a
<lb id="L02L089" n="089"/>little several times, &amp; this
<lb id="L02L090" n="090"/>afternoon while I was rubbing
<lb id="L02L091" n="091"/>his arm, he was saying
<lb id="L02L092" n="092"/>something &mdash; &amp; then said something
<lb id="L02L093" n="093"/>I did not hear. <q>What did
<lb id="L02L094" n="094"/>you say</q> I asked. <q>It <unclear reason="illegible">
                     <del type="overstrike" hand="SPH">belies</del>
                  </unclear>
<lb id="L02L095" n="095"/>was nothing to the purpose, he
<lb id="L02L096" n="096"/>replied. <hi rend="underline">I was wandering</hi>.</q>
<lb id="L02L097" n="097"/>I never saw such clearness. He
<lb id="L02L098" n="098"/>looks from some high place
<lb id="L02L099" n="099"/>even upon his aberrations.
<lb id="L02L100" n="100"/>I can write no more now
<lb id="L02L101" n="101"/>I <sic corr="received">received</sic> a blessed refreshment
<lb id="L02L102" n="102"/>yesterday P.M. beside <name type="person">
                  <sic corr="Mr.">Mr</sic>
<lb id="L02L103" n="103"/>Taylor</name>, a long &mdash; closely written letter</p>

<closer>
<lb/> Your most aff<abbr expan="ectionate">ectionate</abbr>
<lb/> <signed>
                  <name type="sender" reg="Hawthorne, Sophia Peabody (1809-1871)">Sophy</name>
               </signed>
               <lb id="L02L106" n=""/>
               <add place="Left margin" hand="SPH">
		My love to <name type="person">Connie</name><note target="n10">10</note>
               </add>
            </closer>
         </div1>
      </body>
