            <head>Notes</head>
            <note id="n1">1. Sophia Hawthorne's sister Elizabeth Palmer Peabody (1804-1894). <bibl>ANB</bibl></note>
            <note id="n2">2. Edward Thompson Taylor (1793-1871, a Methodist preacher and minister for nearly forty years at the 
               Seamen's Bethel, Boston, Massachusetts. <bibl>CEN 15:421-22; Mott</bibl>
            </note>
            <note id="n3">3. George Francis Peabody (1813-1839), Sophia's brother, who suffered from spinal tuberculosis, died in Elizabeth's care on November 25, 1839, six days after the writing of this letter. <bibl>CEN 15; 360-375</bibl>
            </note>
            <note id="n4">4. Elizabeth Palmer Peabody (1778-1853), Sophia's mother. <bibl>Turner 103</bibl>
            </note>
            <note id="n5">5. Dr. Nathaniel Peabody (1774-1855, Sophia's father. <bibl>Turner 103</bibl>
            </note>
            <note id="n6">6. Elizabeth Palmer Peabody, who was in . . . 
            </note>
            <note id="n7">7. Sophia Hawthorne's sister, Mary Tyler Peabody Mann (1807-1887). <bibl>CEN 15:25</bibl></note>
            <note id="n8">8. Sophia Hawthorne.</note>
            <note id="n9">9. Sophia Palmer Pickman (1786-1862), Sophia Hawthorne's aunt. CEN 16:14</note>
            <note id="n10">10. Unidentified.</note>
